metadata.name: Warped Manhattan
metadata.description:
When the pandemic started, photography took a turn for me. I couldn't follow through with some plans I had, so I turned to creating art pieces instead.

"Our passions are the true phoenixes; when the old one is burnt out, a new one rises from its ashes."
- Johann Wolfgang von Goethe

"Warped Manhattan" is a piece that is intended to have many different meanings and was inspired by the Golden Spiral, 3D glasses, and the allure of a martini. 

Photographed Sept 9 2020.
